hat have relocated Dante’s visions of heaven and hell to urban American settings. This study also includes a guide that showcases selected treasures from the extensive Dante collections at the Library of Congress, illustrating the depth and variety of The Divine Comedy’s global influence. The Unexpected Dante is thus a boon to both Dante scholars and aficionados of this literary masterpiece. Published by Bucknell University Press in association with the Library of Congress. Distributed worldwide by Rutgers University Press.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aDante Alighieri, Henry Wadsworth Longfellow, Cato, Sandow Birk, Musical instruments, Incunabula, Nicolaus de Laurentii, Commedia, Roman Law, The Divine Comedy, European Literature, art, literary studies, cultural studies.1 aAlbro, Sylvia R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbro, Sylvia Rodgers, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiabattoni, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayden, Carla D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlson, Kristina M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiciché, Bernardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolf, Lucia Alma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolf, Lucia Alma, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978168448359440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781684483594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781684483594/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers Universit